----
This paragraph gives the results of multiplications and divisions
of the form
----
$$
  \begin{aligned}
    (4 \cdot 3^n) \times (3^{n + 1}) &= 4 \cdot 3^{2 n + 1} \\
    (4 \cdot 3^{2 n + 1}) \div (2 \cdot 3^n) &= 2 \cdot 3^{n + 1},
  \end{aligned}
$$
----
where $n = 1, 2, \dots, 11$.
